        "title": "Dogs LOVE these!",
        "link": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/customer-reviews/R1OL25ZG8OXXE/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8",
        "text": "I was skeptical at first. I have a hot apartment with only a rolling a/c unit for whatever room we are in. We are in the desert southwest and our days average 100 degrees. My dogs pant from sun up to sun down. Whenever I pull their bandanas out of the freezer, they’re little tails wag, and they can’t run to me fast enough. It keeps them cool for a bout 1-1.5 hours and then I rewet them and back in the freezer they go. They take about ten minutes to freeze. I ordered whatever size was offered, I think medium? Anyway, the frogs are two chihuahua terrier mixes under 30 lbs each and they’re a tad big but I think they are perfect. I would recommend getting one size bigger if that’s an option so it covers more dog! Lol",
